extends ../../docs-template-partials/_docs-article

block prepend article
  - var articleId = "basics-tables"
  - var articleTitle = "Text Tables"

block section
  
  p This is what a basic (classless) table looks like using Codebase:
  
  table
    thead
      tr
        th Table Header 1
        th Table Header 2
        th Table Header 3
    tbody
      tr
        td Table content 1.1
        td Table content 2.1
        td Table content 3.1
      tr
        td Table content 1.2
        td Table content 2.2
        td Table content 3.2
      tr
        td Table content 1.3
        td Table content 2.3
        td Table content 3.3
  
  p.mt--line No styling whatsoever is applied to the #[code &lt;table&gt;] tag by Codebase. So there is nothing that will interfere with other frameworks or plugins if you use them.

  p For more functionality and styling, see the Codebase #[a(href="components.html#components-responsive-table") table component]. 
